  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "If the scheduler is not healthy, pods won't schedule and things will get stuck in pending.\n\nRight now, there is no user visible feedback (in logs or events or pod status) that indicates that this is true.\n\nWe should really have at least some logging in the apiserver, and possibly more in-depth information.\n\nI'm thinking that we should add a /validatez handler to the apiserver that does a quick sanity check.\n\nAdded bonus: we could rip out all of the scripted health checking in the startup scripts.\n",
